The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 March is 41,234 (4,772.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 March, there were 281 new confirmed cases (32.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 March, there were 286 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (5 fewer cases).
